  <section id="Section518552" role="openmfg">
    <title>Create Planned Order</title>

    <para id="Para518553">To create a Planned Order, select the "Create
    Planned Order" option. The following screen will appear:</para>

    <para id="Para518557"><screenshot>
        <mediaobject>
          <imageobject>
            <imagedata fileref="images/MS_Sched_createPlanOrd.png"
                       id="Graphic520435" />
          </imageobject>

          <caption id="Caption518558">Create Planned Order</caption>
        </mediaobject>
      </screenshot></para>

    <para id="Para518564">When creating a Planned Order, you are presented
    with the following options:</para>

    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para518565">Planned Order #</term>

        <listitem>
          <para>Displays system-defined Planned Order Number.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para518567">Item Number</term>

        <listitem>
          <para>Enter the Item Number of the Item you want to create a Planned
          Order for.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para553572">UOM</term>

        <listitem>
          <para>Inventory Unit of Measure.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para532107">Warehouse</term>

        <listitem>
          <para>Specify Warehouse for Planned Order.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para532111">Qty. Ordered</term>

        <listitem>
          <para>Enter the quantity of the specified Item required for the
          Planned Order.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para518581">Due Date</term>

        <listitem>
          <para>Enter the date the Planned Order must be completed by.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para518583">Start Date</term>

        <listitem>
          <para>This date will be equal to the due date less the Lead Time.
          The start date may be changed by altering the Lead Time
          field.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para518585"><anchor id="Anchor528671" role="Index"
        xreflabel="lead times:in planned orders;planned orders:lead times for" />
        <indexterm significance="normal" zone="Anchor528671">
            <primary>lead times</primary>

            <secondary>in planned orders</secondary>
          </indexterm> <indexterm significance="normal" zone="Anchor528671">
            <primary>planned orders</primary>

            <secondary>lead times for</secondary>
          </indexterm>Lead Time (Days)</term>

        <listitem>
          <para>Select a number using the arrow buttons, or manually enter a
          value up to a maximum of 999.</para>

          <para id="Para518586">Value entered specifies the Lead Time required
          between the Due Date and the Start Date.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>

    <para id="Para518587">To the far right of the screen, the following
    buttons are available:</para>

    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para518588">CLOSE</term>

        <listitem>
          <para>Closes the screen without creating the Planned Order,
          returning you to the application desktop.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term id="Para518589">CREATE</term>

        <listitem>
          <para>Creates the Planned Order.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </section>